{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7f98474b-ea4b-4088-9bc0-00b504de77e4","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Flag mapping:**\n\n| VSTest | MTP (after `--`) |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter` | `--filter` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Prerequisites** — add these NuGet packages to your test project:\n\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\nOn .NET 8 the `--` separator is required because `dotnet test` still defaults to the VSTest runner. Everything after `--` is forwarded to MTP. If you add `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to your project file, you can drop the `--`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bcfa22c3-03d1-4be9-9f0e-4aac57d5788f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` (or using Microsoft.CodeCoverage collector)\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith .NET 8, you'd still use `dotnet test` but pass MTP-specific options after `--`, since native MTP support in `dotnet test` came with .NET 9 SDK. With .NET 8 and MTP, I need to either enable `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in the project file or run the test executable directly. The command-line flags map across: `--filter` stays the same, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`, code coverage requires the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` package and uses `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`, and the blame options translate to `--crashdump`, `--hangdump`, and `--hangdump-timeout`.","outputTokens":1267,"requestId":"984B:29E2AD:173736:1E74D9:69FFD845"},"id":"b1935127-c7ce-4f69-b8ad-4dede2216599","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:59:07.266Z","parentId":"13d86ee4-1b12-4d31-9d8b-eaa527c719ad"}
